                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="39682" author="adilger" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 20:19:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fix is landed for e2fsprogs-1.42.3.wc1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39680" author="adilger" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 20:05:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New fix in &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/2986&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/2986&lt;/a&gt;, which also passes the RHEL5 build.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39642" author="adilger" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 16:13:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was caused by a patch change when pushing the patch upstream.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fix for the problem is in &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/2985&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/2985&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39589" author="pjones" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 13:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas is working on this one&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39584" author="sarah" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 13:11:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this also affects 1.8.8 RHEL6 build&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39571" author="chris" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 09:32:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My guess is that actually it&apos;s really post install.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The loadjenkins install via chef installs el6 and then installs the lustre kernel it is after this reboot with the b2_2 kernel that the fs appears to be corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
